ISLAMABAD, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan on Saturday registered 609 new COVID-19 cases and three more deaths, the National Command and Operation Center (NCOC) said on Sunday. The NCOC said that the total tally of COVID-19 cases has risen to 1,518,692, including 1,470,424 recoveries from the pandemic. There are 17,961 active cases in the Asian country, including 600 patients in critical condition. According to the NCOC data, three more people died from COVID-19 on Saturday, bringing the death toll to 30,307. Pakistan's southern Sindh province is the most affected region in terms of the number of cases, with 571,854 infections, followed by the eastern Punjab province which has reported 503,715 cases.  â– 